cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper focuses on reducing computation costs in convolutional neural networks (CNNs) which are widely used in computer vision tasks. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a new approach for optimizing neural networks and discusses the influence of the new similarity measure on the optimization process. 
3. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a new type of neural network architecture (AdderNets) that reduces the number of multiplications in deep learning. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a new approach for optimizing neural networks that could have implications for the broader field of artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the computational complexity of multiplication operations in deep learning and proposes a new approach that relies on cheaper addition operations.
